text.tspan: Seventy seven children were born in a hospital between 1-11 January 1986 (winter).
Between 1-11 July in the same year (summer), sixty four children were born in this
hospital. The genders of the children are shown in the table below.
Does the proportion of male babies tend to be the same in summer and
winter? If there is a difference, by how much?
